<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.428/576</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Polk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March 23,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 183</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At the request of the Canadian
                                Government I have the honour to call your attention to the fact that
                                the signature of the Treaty between the United States and Great
                                Britain concerning port privileges of fishing vessels, lobster
                                fishing, halibut fishing, and Tariff on fresh fish, the draft<note n="4" xml:id="d408fn4"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_258"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 258</ref>.</note> of which
                                was prepared by negotiation between Sir Douglas Hazen and the
                                Department of State, is still outstanding. The Government of the
                                Dominion will be glad to learn at what date the United States
                                Government will be prepared to proceed to the signature of this
                                Treaty.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. C.
                                Lindsay</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>